The paper explores the loss landscape of neural networks, which is a topic typically studied in the machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. The use of fully-connected and convolutional neural networks also suggests a potential fit for the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the suitability of network initialization, which is a topic relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT).
